OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1779440815
OL,3,CWoman with cancer 'furious' that
OL,4,Cassisted dying bill failed at House of
OL,5,CLords
OL,7,FA terminally ill woman from Devon says
OL,8,Fshe is furious that a bill, which
OL,9,Fcould have made assisted dying legal
OL,10,Fin England and Wales, failed at the
OL,11,FHouse of Lords.
OL,13,FClare Turner, 61, has breast cancer
OL,14,Fwhich has spread to her bones.
OL,16,FShe wants to die in her garden, under
OL,17,Fher favourite tree, surrounded by
OL,18,Ffriends and her two daughters.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1779440815
OL,3,CWoman with cancer 'furious' that
OL,4,Cassisted dying bill failed at House of
OL,5,CLords
OL,7,F"I don't look upon myself as being a
OL,8,Fvictim, we've all got to die
OL,9,Fsometime," she said.
OL,11,F"I look upon myself as being a
OL,12,Freflective, well-informed, reasonably
OL,13,Fintelligent person who would like to
OL,14,Fmake choices in life about myself."
OL,16,FOn 24 April 2026 the Terminally Ill
OL,17,FAdults (End of Life) Bill ran out of
OL,18,Ftime in the House of Lords, which
OL,19,Fmeans it will not become law.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1779440815
OL,3,CWoman with cancer 'furious' that
OL,4,Cassisted dying bill failed at House of
OL,5,CLords
OL,7,FThe bill would have allowed terminally
OL,8,Fill adults with less than six months
OL,9,Fto live to apply for an assisted death
OL,10,Fif approval was given by a panel of
OL,11,Fhealthcare and legal professionals.
OL,13,FMPs - who are elected by voters in the
OL,14,FUK - voted in favour of the bill in
OL,15,F2025.
OL,17,FThe House of Lords is unelected and is
OL,18,Fmade up of around 800 peers who are
OL,19,Frecommended by the House of Lords
OL,20,FAppointments Commission and approved
OL,21,Fby the Prime Minister.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1779440815
OL,3,CWoman with cancer 'furious' that
OL,4,Cassisted dying bill failed at House of
OL,5,CLords
OL,7,FWhile opponents of the bill called it
OL,8,F"hopelessly flawed", supporters
OL,9,Faccused some Lords of 'filibustering':
OL,10,Fdeliberately prolonging the debate so
OL,11,Fthe bill would run out of time and
OL,12,Ffail.
OL,14,F"I'm furious about it, actually.
OL,15,FReally, really angry. I don't see how
OL,16,Fwe can call our country a democracy if
OL,17,Fthis sort of thing can happen," Clare
OL,18,Fsaid.
OL,20,F"It's shaken my faith in our
OL,21,Fdemocratic process."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1779440815
OL,3,CWoman with cancer 'furious' that
OL,4,Cassisted dying bill failed at House of
OL,5,CLords
OL,7,FSupporters of the bill are campaigning
OL,8,Fto have the bill reintroduced in the
OL,9,Fnext Private Members Bill ballot on 21
OL,10,FMay, which is the next opportunity for
OL,11,FMPs to propose a bill.
OL,13,FIt's a ballot - so MP's can put
OL,14,Fforward their bills and the chosen
OL,15,Fones are selected at random. In
OL,16,Ftheory, an MP could put assisted dying
OL,17,Fin the ballot and it be re-debated
OL,18,Fthat way. However, lots of MPs put
OL,19,Fbills forward so the chances of
OL,20,Fgetting selected are already low.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1779440815
OL,3,CWoman with cancer 'furious' that
OL,4,Cassisted dying bill failed at House of
OL,5,CLords
OL,7,FIf they aren't selected high up in the
OL,8,Fdraw, there may not be enough time to
OL,9,Fdebate the bill and it could result in
OL,10,Fa similar situation to what we have
OL,11,Fseen this time round.
OL,13,F"I'd like to leave this world feeling
OL,14,Fgrateful, and thinking 'how lucky am I
OL,15,Fthat I've had such a wonderful, rich
OL,16,Fexistence?'" Claire said.
OL,18,F"There's no way I'm going to allow my
OL,19,Fdaughters to be traumatised by my
OL,20,Fpassing."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
